video_title: simple tips for good mental health #shorts
video_description: mental health is just as important as physical health in this video we will discuss 10 simple tips for good mental health including get enough sleep sleep is essential for mental health when you don t get enough sleep you re more likely to experience anxiety depression and other mental health problems eat a healthy diet eating a healthy diet can help to improve your mood and energy levels it can also help to reduce stress and anxiety exercise regularly exercise is a great way to relieve stress and improve your mood it can also help to improve your sleep quality spend time with loved ones social connection is important for mental health make time for the people you care about and who care about you learn to manage stress stress can take a toll on your mental health learn to manage stress in healthy ways such as yoga meditation or deep breathing set realistic goals don t set yourself up for failure by setting unrealistic goals set goals that are challenging but achievable take breaks it s important to take breaks from work school and other activities take some time for yourself to relax and recharge do things you enjoy make time for activities that you enjoy doing things you love can help to improve your mood and reduce stress seek professional help if needed if you re struggling with your mental health don t hesitate to seek professional help a therapist can help you to develop coping mechanisms and strategies for managing your mental health #mentalhealth #selfcare #wellness #tipsforgoodmentalhealth #sleep #diet #exercise #socialconnection #stressmanagement #goals #breaks #enjoyment #therapy

video_title: living well with schizophrenia
audio_transcript: hello everybody this is gary today is sunday december 25th 2022 it s christmas day it s 509 p m eastern standard time in the united states in rochester new york and this is my coping with schizophrenia blog entry for today today my auditory hallucinations are not that bad my paranoia and delusions are not that bad my anxiety levels are pretty high my physical pain in my right knee is pretty intense my depression is not that bad today today i didn t do much for christmas i just stayed home i did go outside earlier for my physical therapy and walking exercises and it s cold as hell outside there s not much snow on the ground but it s very very cold in rochester new york i m seeing my new therapist this upcoming wednesday on the 28th today s the 25th i was told that i had a new therapist when i went to see my therapist last week and my old therapist is going to sit in on the meeting with my new therapist to make sure that the transfer is as smooth as possible and any wrinkles are ironed out between me and my new therapist i m not sure how often i ll be seeing my new therapist to begin with i would like to see them more frequently to get to know her better my man is a woman and my last therapist was also a woman which is what i requested i don t do well with male therapists it often gets very confrontational when i have a male therapist so i did request a female therapist and that s what i m getting i m seeing my psychiatrist week after next i don t suspect to be changing any of my medications or anything like that i doubt that there s going to be any need to make any changes to my medication we already reduced my zyprexa the antipsychotic that i use for paranoia because it caused possible urinary retention which i had to go to the emergency room a couple weeks ago they had to insert a urinary catheter and we didn t remove it until a week and a half later then i spent some time in the emergency department for possible internal bleeding but physically i m doing okay it s just that i have a lot of pain in my right knee i had surgery on may 13th earlier this year and the pain in my right knee and the stiffness is still there that s why i try to exercise my knee and my legs every day to reduce the stiffness and pain i still take tylenol for pain i m still on cymbaltha for physical pain narotin for physical pain flexeril for physical muscle pain and like i said i m still taking tylenol i m still on 600 milligrams of seroquel at night as an antipsychotic and mood stabilizer i m still on my stomach medications i m still on my blood pressure medications i m still on all the other medications that i was on before nothing has changed in that regard my primary care hasn t changed any of my medical medications i m still going to see my primary care provider i believe in march or april next year sometime around there something like that in february i m seeing the urologist just to follow up on the urinary retention but beyond that there s nothing else to report on i hope everybody has a merry christmas

audio_transcript: what effect does christmas have on mental health here s what research tells us christmastime is associated with increased dysphoria and loneliness there are many reasons for this including financial stress alcohol use lack of exercise family conflict time pressure social obligations and overindulgence christmastime is associated with lower emotional well being and lower life satisfaction people are generally more dissatisfied around christmas there s the sense that for many people christmas has become a stressful time because it puts a lot of demands on them i think many people want christmas to be perfect like they set the bar really high trying to achieve that standard is a lot of work and often impossible based on this one could make an argument that simplicity and low expectations around the holidays could lead to a more joyful celebration

video_title: from stress to success 5 tips for improving your mental health #shorts #mentalhealth #stress
video_description: stress stress is a normal and natural response to challenging situations it s important to learn how to manage stress effectively to prevent it from taking a toll on our wellbeing here are some tips to help you manage stress number 1 exercise regularly exercise is a great way to reduce stress and boost your mood it releases endorphins which are natural mood boosters so try to make time for exercise in your daily routine 2 practice mindfulness mindfulness is a technique that involves being fully present in the moment and accepting your thoughts and feelings without judgment it can help reduce stress and improve your overall wellbeing you can try mindfulness meditation deep breathing exercises or yoga 3 prioritize self care make sure to take care of yourself by getting enough sleep eating a balanced diet and doing things that make you happy taking time for yourself can help reduce stress and improve your overall quality of life 4 connect with others social support is important for managing stress make time to connect with friends and family or join a support group talking to others about your problems can help you feel less alone and more supported 5 seek professional help if needed if you re feeling overwhelmed or unable to manage your stress on your own don t be afraid to seek professional help a therapist or counselor can help you develop coping skills and strategies to manage stress effectively

video_description: breathing into paper bag during panic attack #hyperventilation #panicattack #anxiety #anxietytips #scienceexplained
audio_transcript: oh my gosh i m starting to feel anxious i saw on tv i should breathe into this paper bag have you ever wondered why doctors would tell people to breathe into a paper bag in a movie when they start to hyperventilate well the answer is when you breathe too fast you breathe off all of the carbon dioxide in your lungs in exchange for the oxygen that you re breathing in when you breathe off the carbon dioxide it causes the ph of your blood to rise when the ph rises the calcium level drops and you start to get that numbness and tingling of your hands and fingertips and around your mouth if it progresses your hands are actually going to spasm all the way up and temporarily you won t be able to use them so in the old days they would tell them to breathe into a paper bag with the thought that you d be breathing back in that carbon dioxide to prevent that process from happening now we don t routinely recommend this anymore because it s hard to regulate but if you want to learn more about this and other wacky things hit that follow button

fired from my command for writing a book trying to reverse the trend of the overt politicization of the uniformed services specifically i criticized the military s diversity equity and inclusion trainings which at my own base were illegally occurring despite an executive order from the commander in chief the diversity equity and inclusion industry is steeped in critical race theory and is rooted in anti american marxist ideology i watched dei trainings divide our troops ideologically and in some cases sow the seeds of animosity toward the very country they had sworn an oath to defend before writing that book i submitted a formal written complaint to the space force inspector general s office detailing that such violations were occurring including illegal race based discrimination but my complaint was never investigated and was later dismissed by then lieutenant general stephen whiting whom the senate just confirmed for his fourth star after two months i received a written dismissal of my complaint from general whiting personally i have always advocated for a non political military work environment today i m here to testify about the ongoing marxist inspired efforts to subvert and weaken our military and broader american society we often refer to these efforts as wokeism but it is also a culture war yet even in this committee there are differing views about whether there is such a thing as a culture war underway some members of this committee have been outspoken critics of dei initiatives to include crt drag shows on military bases trans activism lgbtq pride celebrations and woke military recruiting videos all things that are visible components of an ongoing culture war ranking member garcia as he just mentioned on the other hand and asserted as recently as two weeks ago says that the culture wars are quote unquote phony and are merely a political talking point of republicans it s nothing if not incredible for a member of this subcommittee to assert that culture wars are phony while another member who s not present at the moment of this committee is a member of the so called progressive squad was herself a black lives matter organizer and activist an organization whose publicly avowed ideology is marxism and whose activist ambition is social and cultural revolution service members who wear the uniform of their country do not want to see these things in the military workplace they don t want to see them at their bases in most cases this is true regardless of their race or their political worldview despite that reality pentagon officials requested 140 million to expand woke diversity initiatives in fiscal year 2024 double what it s been the previous two years there are few things taxpayers such as myself feel less essential to the mission of the united states military than expanding diversity mandates and indoctrination and now an important point such aggressively opposed ideological worldviews competing for institutionalization through policy epitomizes and formalizes what is properly termed a culture war the fact that these debates now infect the u s military workplace is an offense to people like me who love their country and all people regardless of their race gender sexual preference or background

video_title: how can bipolar disorder affect relationships #shorts #bipolar #mentalhealth
video_description: how can bipolar disorder affect relationships bipolar disorder is a mental health condition characterized by extreme mood swings including episodes of mania or hypomania highs and depression lows bipolar disorder can affect relationships in various ways unpredictability the mood swings associated with bipolar disorder can create uncertainty and instability in the relationship making it difficult for both partners to know what to expect emotional strain the extreme emotions experienced during manic and depressive episodes can be challenging for both partners to cope with leading to emotional distress communication difficulties the symptoms of bipolar disorder such as racing thoughts or irritability can make it difficult for partners to communicate effectively and resolve conflicts impulsive behavior during manic or hypomanic episodes a person with bipolar disorder may engage in impulsive or risky behavior which can strain the relationship and create trust issues social isolation the depressive symptoms of bipolar disorder may lead to social withdrawal making it difficult for partners to maintain a healthy social life and support network if you suspect your partner has bipolar disorder encourage them to seek professional help from a mental health specialist it s also essential to educate yourself about the condition practice empathy and maintain open communication couples therapy and support groups can be helpful resources for both partners to navigate the challenges associated with bipolar disorder in a relationship

video_title: a beautiful mind schizophrenia explained can be treated #shorts #johnnash #schizophrenia
video_description: in this video a beautiful mind schizophrenia explained we will be briefly touching on schizophrenia a severe mental health condition that affects approximately 1 of the population one well known example of schizophrenia is the life of john nash a nobel prize winning mathematician whose story was depicted in the movie a beautiful mind the symptoms of schizophrenia can vary from person to person but typically fall into three categories positive symptoms negative symptoms and cognitive symptoms positive symptoms refer to experiences that are added to a person s behavior or thoughts while negative symptoms refer to experiences that are removed from a person s behavior or thoughts cognitive symptoms refer to difficulties with memory attention and decision making one example of positive symptoms is hallucinations which can involve seeing hearing or feeling things that are not there in a beautiful mind john nash experiences auditory hallucinations in the form of imaginary people who he believed were his colleagues and friends these hallucinations can be extremely distressing and can make it difficult to distinguish between reality and fiction another example of positive symptoms is delusions such as those john nash had in a beautiful mind which are false beliefs that are not based in reality in the movie john nash becomes convinced that he is a secret agent working for the government and that his hallucinations are part of his job these delusions can be dangerous if they lead to behaviors that are harmful to oneself or others negative symptoms can include a lack of motivation difficulty expressing emotions and a loss of pleasure in activities that were once enjoyable in a beautiful mind john nash experiences a lack of motivation to continue his work as a mathematician despite his natural talent and passion for the subject this lack of motivation can make it difficult to function in daily life and can impact relationships and work cognitive symptoms can include difficulty with memory attention and decision making in the movie john nash struggles with social interactions and has difficulty understanding social cues and norms these cognitive symptoms can make it difficult to perform daily tasks and can impact overall quality of life it s important to note that there are additional symptoms of schizophrenia beyond those depicted in the movie for example some people with schizophrenia may experience disordered speech such as rambling or using nonsensical language they may also exhibit abnormal movements such as repetitive motions or unusual postures while there is no cure for schizophrenia it can be treated with a combination of medication therapy and support antipsychotic medication can help alleviate positive symptoms such as hallucinations and delusions while therapy can help individuals develop coping skills and improve social interactions support from family and friends can also play a crucial role in managing the symptoms of schizophrenia in conclusion schizophrenia is a complex and often debilitating mental health condition that can impact all aspects of a person s life while the symptoms can vary from person to person they typically fall into three categories positive symptoms negative symptoms and cognitive symptoms it s important to recognize that there are additional symptoms beyond those depicted in popular media and that schizophrenia can be treated with a combination of medication therapy and support by reducing symptoms and improving quality of life individuals with schizophrenia can lead fulfilling and meaningful lives #microdosetherapy #schizophrenia #abeautifulmind #johnnash music from #uppbeat free for creators uppbeat io t tobias voigt machina
audio_transcript: john nash in a beautiful mind experienced hallucinations and delusions but schizophrenia has other symptoms as well such as disorganized speech abnormal movements or a lack of motivation with its symptoms ranging from mild to severe schizophrenia is a complex disorder myths and stigmas surrounding schizophrenia prevent people from seeking help although there are effective treatments we can create an inclusive society for those with schizophrenia by increasing awareness so what myths have you heard this is microdose therapy your daily dose of psych

audio_transcript: so most of the patients that we have in the gems clinic actually know their gender usually around the age of puberty but a good portion of children do know as early as seemingly from the womb and they will usually express their gender identity as very young children some as soon as they can talk they might say phrases such as i m a girl or i m a boy or i m going to be a woman or i m going to be a mom kids know very very early so in the gems clinic we see a variety of young children all the way down to ages two and three and usually up to the ages of nine when they come into the clinic they ll see one of our psychologists and we ll be talking to them about their gender we ll be talking to their family about how to best support that child and how to make sure that that child has the space and support to explore their gender and do well throughout their development and we ll be answering any parent questions a lot of parents do have questions and so we answer those questions the biggest piece of advice i give parents who are coming through the gender clinic at boston children s hospital is to just be supportive sometimes you might not understand sometimes you feel like you don t know the terms or you don t kind of get exactly what the child means when they say that they might be this gender but the biggest thing you can do is just love your child and support them and just allow them to express themselves that s the biggest protector as well against negative mental health effects such as depression suicidality anxiety that we worry about for our gender diverse kids and young adults so that support from a parent is one of the best protective factors and one of the best things they can do

video_title: adderall addicts unleashed savage live media savagelive 4 2 2024 11am
video_description: adderall addicts unleashed savage live media savagelive 4 2 2024 11am the hunt while countless friends had prescriptions for my newfound friend i knew my younger brother had recently stopped taking his prescription due to the appetite loss side effect when i went home for break after finals i located the bottle beneath my parents bathroom sink and dumped out a hundred or so into my palm scurrying back to my bedroom i immediately smashed out a few lines and was flying high for the afternoon nevermind that i had to care for my brother adderall had taken hold within two weeks of returning to school i was carrying a pre crushed jar of powder in my backpack with one end of a tampon applicator to snort it it took less than that amount of time to run through what i had stolen from my brother fueled by a diet of prescription amphetamines coffee alcohol weed and cigarettes i began to pilfer from my friends prescriptions they would give me some and i always took a few extra for the road justifying it with the reasoning that they would have more next month they only needed it to study i needed it to survive or so i thought the comedown my run with adderall was a sporadic and passionate love affair there were times my ability to find it would dry up and i would slave through the weeks of frustration agitation and cravings then i would find another friend with a prescription and repeat the process all over again it all culminated when the adderall alcohol marijuana and other drugs landed me at the end of my senior year with three uncompleted classes three weeks before graduation i knew there was nothing normal about the amount of substances i used i couldn t do anything without smoking a bowl snorting a line or swallowing a shot a caring professor sat me down after class one day and mentioned the papers i had produced throughout the year she brought up the allusions to substance abuse peppered throughout my work the run on sentences and rambling thoughts fueled by legal amphetamines she explained to me that she had just celebrated 10 years of sobriety in march using a program with a path to sobriety she told me her story of swigging from bottles beneath her desk before classes started it was as though she was looking into my mind reading the thoughts as they raced through my brain she knew me and she didn t even know me she put me in touch with another student in the program who took me to my first meeting i was astounded at the things these people shared amazed that i felt the same way they did still wary of giving up my drugs i went to a few meetings high after a couple of weeks though something stuck and i found myself sober for days at a time

video_title: understanding self harm is it a big deal #shorts
video_description: is self harm a big deal the answer is yes it is a big deal if you or someone you know is experiencing intense and painful emotions it is important to know that things can get better and that you can learn to cope in many healthy ways that don t make things worse for you the first step is to talk to a friend or adult whom you trust it will help to know that you are not alone and that people accept and support you if you learn to depend on cutting or self harm as a way to cope with your feelings it can become a habit that s really difficult to stop even if you want to if you feel like you can t bring up your difficulties to someone you know a confidential conversation with a counselor will be a helpful place to start text start to 741 741 for a free confidential chat with a counselor or call 1 800 273 talk 8255 24 7 to talk to someone about what you re going through in this video stephanie cherestal phd jed expert offers guidance to those at risk of self harm she states that engaging in self harm can actually get in the way of learning healthier and more helpful ways of dealing with painful emotions self harm can be treated and a lot of the treatments involve teaching deliberate skills to manage intense emotions without engaging in self harm learn more about self harm and explore treatment options so you or a loved one can begin to heal and seek support the jed foundation jed is a nonprofit that protects emotional health and prevents suicide for our nation s teens and young adults if you are experiencing a mental health crisis text or call 988 to get resources or get involved visit #mentalhealth #therapy #jed #selfharm #suicide
audio_transcript: so a lot of times people ask me if i m not suicidal i m not trying to end my life is self harm such a big deal and i always say yes it is a big deal engaging in self harm might feel like a strategy to bring down intensely painful emotions but it s really an ineffective strategy that can create a lot more problems than it solves even though a lot of people who are engaging in self harm are not actually suicidal research has actually shown that there is a link between self harm and suicide we ve actually found that people who engage in self harm tend to be at higher risk for suicide later on a lot of things that you don t intend can stem from self harm things like infections from the cuts that are left on your body engaging in self harm can actually get in the way of learning healthier and more helpful ways of dealing with painful emotions there are a lot of different treatments that help treat self harm a lot of those treatments involve teaching deliberate skills to manage intense emotions without engaging in self harm

video_title: start low go slow panic attacks antidepressants ssris snris
video_description: ssris selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors and snris serotonin norepinephrine reuptake inhibitors are two classes of antidepressants that are commonly prescribed to treat panic attacks they are very effective but in many patients if they are started at the usual starting doses used when treating depression they may make panic attacks and overall anxiety worse initially therefore the safest course of action is to start them at 1 4 to 1 2 of the normal starting doses initially and then increase them as necessary and as tolerated some common examples escitalopram lexapro normal starting dose 10 mg start at 5 mg or less sertraline zoloft normal starting dose is 50 mg start at 25 mg or less paroxetine paxil normal starting dose 20 mg start at 10 mg or less fluoxetine prozac normal starting dose 20 mg start at 10 mg or less citalopram celexa normal starting dose 20 mg start at 10 mg or less who am i i m dr jeff knuppel a psychiatrist m d with over 20 years of practice experience my goal is to create helpful and interesting videos about mental health wellness personal growth and substance abuse topics this is a new channel if you find the content helpful i greatly appreciate your support by liking and subscribing thank you #shorts #panicdisorder
audio_transcript: if you re having panic attacks there s one crucial detail that you need to know about antidepressants that some prescribers are not aware of medications such as the ssris usually work very well but if they re not prescribed correctly they may worsen your panic attacks initially the solution is to start them at one quarter to one half of the normal starting dose and then to increase them slowly as tolerated

video_title: how fitness helps mental health #shorts
video_description: how does exercise help my mental health exercise causes your brain to release feel good chemicals like endorphins and serotonin that help improve your mood it also improves your fitness which can help lift your mood doing physical activity can also distract you from negative thought patterns how much exercise do i need australian guidelines recommend adults do at least 30 minutes of moderate to intensive physical activity on most or all days of the week combine your exercise routine with a healthy diet and other healthy lifestyle habits while you exercise you can also practice steady breathing for self awareness focus on keeping a good posture how do i start exercising when starting to exercise it s important to stay within your limits if you are not usually active start with simple activities like going to the shops gardening household chores cooking at your own pace try to build up to doing 30 minutes of moderate exercise each day such as bike riding walking swimming if you have a pedometer or smart watch you can also monitor your steps and set walking goals at first aim for around 1 000 steps a day eventually try to aim for 8 000 to 10 000 steps per day you don t need to visit a gym to exercise you can start exercising in a comfortable environment to build your confidence you can exercise at home outside alone with people you know or with a class or group consider ways you can incorporate exercise into your daily routine and lifestyle when starting exercise pick something you enjoy you can use your friends or family as motivators to keep you on track enjoy the benefits of owning a pet if you own a dog make the most of your local area for their walks you could walk in a park or by a beach if they are nearby if you enjoy dancing try a creative dance movement class if you enjoy art visit a museum or gallery how do i overcome obstacles to exercising when starting exercise you may experience some barriers but they can be overcome motivation and energy mental health issues can be tiring you may struggle with motivation for exercise to overcome this you can start slow and set small goals reward yourself for exercising try social exercise remind yourself that exercise will help you rest better and feel less tired cost you may think that exercising is too costly gym memberships and home exercise equipment can be expensive there are other more affordable ways to exercise local community centres often have affordable exercise groups see if your community has a free local running group go for a walk around your block explore online exercise classes and exercise apps anxiety or feeling intimidated you might feel uncomfortable exercising in a public place or joining a group exercise class this is perfectly normal to feel more comfortable and build your confidence you can try taking a friend with you to an exercise class exercising in comfortable clothes downloading an appto exercise in your own home time if you are short on time there are things you can try to fit exercise into your routine break exercise into small chunks instead of doing 30 minutes in one go do three lots of 10 minutes in a day try to wake up earlier try to walk around on your lunch break physical limitations you may have physical obstacles such as an injury or disability that makes it difficult to exercise you may benefit from seeing a health professional such as a physiotherapist or exercise physiologist to help you recover they can suggest exercise options suitable for you and help you plan activities resources and support the black dog institute has information on depression and benefits of exercise headspace has information and interactive resources to help you stay active beyond blue has tips for getting active as well as a template to help you plan exercise sane australia has information on ways to look after your physical health including physical activity jean hailes has a weekly activity diary and a list of activities to start with they also have tips on how to implement an exercise program sa health has information on the beneficial effects of walking on mood contact head to health for advice assessment and referral into local mental health services call 1800 595 212 from 8 30am to 5pm on weekdays public holidays excluded if you need more information and support visit mental illness fellowship of australia mifa for resources helplines apps online programs forums

video_title: discover the secrets to anxiety relief #shorts #anxiety disorder
video_description: anxiety is a natural reaction to stress and can be described as a feeling of unease such as worry or fear that can be mild or severe while it can be a normal and healthy response to stressful or challenging situations anxiety can become a problem when it becomes excessive or persistent interfering with daily activities and quality of life anxiety can manifest in various ways including physical symptoms such as increased heart rate sweating trembling and difficulty breathing it can also include emotional symptoms such as irritability nervousness restlessness and a sense of impending danger or panic there are different types of anxiety disorders including generalized anxiety disorder panic disorder social anxiety disorder and phobias these disorders are generally characterized by excessive and persistent anxiety and can be diagnosed and treated by healthcare professionals treatment for anxiety may involve a range of interventions including therapy medication and lifestyle changes cognitive behavioral therapy cbt for example can help individuals learn new coping skills and strategies while medication such as selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors ssris can help manage symptoms if you or someone you know is experiencing anxiety it is important to talk to a healthcare professional for diagnosis and treatment options anxiety is a common and treatable condition and seeking help can lead to improved quality of life and overall wellbeing disclaimer the information and materials contained on nurse vanel s channel are provided for general informational purposes only and therefore are no substitute for informed medical advice or treatment consult a medical doctor to seek treatment for any illnesses or medical concern #generalisedanxietydisorder #cbt
